<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-17T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="1388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1388">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.714/10–1849: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-18T01:00:00+08:00">October
                                    18, 1949—1 a. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:22 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1769. Note change October 1 of name Peiping to “Peking”. Believe
                            conformity by American Foreign Service establishments unobjectionable
                            except on one point Nationalist sensibilities, and conformity would
                            avoid one minor point exacerbation Communist feelings. Please
                            instruct.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>